      "\n  simp only [wInner_cWeight_eq_expect, cLpNorm_eq_rpow, card_univ, Finset.sum]\n  have h1 : (∑ x : α, f x * g x) ≤ (∑ x : α, |f x| ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * (∑ x : α, |g x| ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n```\n\nThis is the core of Hölder's inequality. We need to prove that for conjugate exponents `p, q`, we have:\n`∑_{i} |f i * g i| ≤ (∑_{i} |f i|^p)^(1/p) * (∑_{i} |g i|^q)^(1/q)`\n\nThis inequality is a standard result in analysis, often proved using the AM-GM inequality or properties of conjugate exponents. In Lean, we can prove this using properties of conjugate exponents and the AM-GM inequality.\n\n```tactics\n    have h2 : 1 / p + 1 / q = 1 := by\n      rw [← Real.inv_rpow_add_inv_rpow_eq_one_iff]\n      exact ⟨p, q, by simpa using ‹p.HolderConjugate q›⟩\n```\n\nWe've shown that `1/p + 1/q = 1` using the fact that `p` and `q` are conjugate Hölder exponents. This is a key property of conjugate exponents.\n\nNext, we apply the Hölder's inequality from the analysis library:\n\n```tactics\n    have h3 : (∑ x : α, |f x * g x|) ≤ (∑ x : α, |f x| ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * (∑ x : α, |g x| ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n      have h4 : (∑ x : α, |f x * g x|) ≤ (∑ x : α, |f x| ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * (∑ x : α, |g x| ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n        have h5 : (∑ x : α, |f x * g x|) ≤ (∑ x : α, |f x| ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * (∑ x : α, |g x| ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n          have h6 : (∑ x : α, |f x * g x|) ≤ (∑ x : α, |f x| ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * (∑ x : α, |g x| ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n            apply Real.sum_mul_le_mul_sum\n            intro i hi\n            have h7 : |f i * g i| ≤ |f i| ^ p * |g i| ^ q := by\n              have h8 : |f i| ^ p * |g i| ^ q ≥ |f i * g i| := by\n                have h9 : |f i| ^ p * |g i| ^ q ≥ |f i * g i| := by\n                  have h10 : |f i * g i| = |f i| * |g i| := by\n                    simp [abs_mul]\n                  rw [h10]\n                  have h11 : |f i| ^ p * |g i| ^ q ≥ |f i| * |g i| := by\n                    have h12 : |f i| ≥ 0