AM-GM inequality, we need the weights to sum to 1. We have $\\frac{1}{p} + \\frac{1}{q} = 1$.\n\nThe weighted AM-GM inequality for two terms states that for non-negative real numbers $x, y$ and weights $w_1, w_2$ such that $w_1 + w_2 = 1$, we have:\n$$w_1 x + w_2 y \\geq x^{w_1} \\cdot y^{w_2}.$$\n\nIn our case, $x = |f(a)|^p$, $y = |g(a)|^q$, $w_1 = \\frac{1}{p}$, $w_2 = \\frac{1}{q}$.\n\nSo:\n$$\\frac{1}{p} |f(a)|^p + \\frac{1}{q} |g(a)|^q \\geq |f(a)|^{p \\cdot \\frac{1}{p}} \\cdot |g(a)|^{q \\cdot \\frac{1}{q}} = |f(a)|^1 \\cdot |g(a)|^1 = |f(a)| \\cdot |g(a)|.$$\n\nAnd since $f(a) \\cdot g(a) \\leq |f(a)| \\cdot |g(a)|$, we have:\n$$f(a) \\cdot g(a) \\leq |f(a)| \\cdot |g(a)| \\leq \\frac{1}{p} |f(a)|^p + \\frac{1}{q} |g(a)|^q.$$\n\nLet's complete the proof of h1:\n\n```tactics\nhave h2 : |f a| * |g a| ≤ (1 / p : ℝ) * (|f a| : ℝ) ^ p + (1 / q : ℝ) * (|g a| : ℝ) ^ q := by\n  have h3 : (1 / p : ℝ) + (1 / q : ℝ) = 1 := hpq\n```\n\nNow, we need to apply the weighted AM-GM inequality.\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : (|f a| : ℝ) ^ p ≥ 0 := by positivity\nhave h5 : (|g a| : ℝ) ^ q ≥ 0 := by positivity\n```\n\nWe can apply the weighted AM-GM inequality from the math library.\n\n```tactics\nhave h6 : (|f a| : ℝ) ^ p * (|g a| : ℝ) ^ q ≥ 0 := by positivity\n```\n\nThe weighted AM-GM inequality in Lean is `Real.geom_mean_le_arith_mean2_weighted`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h7 : (|f a| : ℝ) ^ p * (|g a| : ℝ) ^ q ≤ ((|f a| : ℝ) ^ p) ^ (1 / p : ℝ) * ((|g a| : ℝ) ^ q) ^ (1 / q : ℝ) := by\n  apply Real.geom_mean_le_arith_mean2_weighted\n  all_goals\n    try { linarith }\n    try { positivity }\n```\n\nWait, this is not the right direction. We need to apply it to the terms $|f(a)|^p$ and $|g(a)|^q$ with weights $\\frac{1}{p}$ and $\\frac{1}{q}$.\n\nWait, the weighted AM-GM inequality should be applied to the terms $|f(a)|^p$ and $|g(a)|^q$.\n\nWait, the weighted AM-GM inequality is for non-negative real numbers $x, y$ and weights $w_1, w_2$ such that $w_1 + w_2 = 1$:\n$$w_1 x + w_2 y \\geq x^