To prove the inequality, we can use the fact that for any real numbers $x, y$ and exponents $p, q$ such that $1/p + 1/q = 1$, we have $x \cdot y \leq \left( \sum |x_i|^p \right)^{1/p} \cdot \left( \sum |y_i|^q \right)^{1/q}$. This is the classical Hölder's inequality.

